CSS Day 3: Box Model (Most Important CSS Topic 🔥)

Every HTML element is a box.

Understanding the Box Model is essential for:

React UI development
Responsive design
Interview questions
Box Model Structure
+-----------------------+
|        Margin         |
|  +-----------------+  |
|  |     Border      |  |
|  | +-------------+ |  |
|  | |   Padding   | |  |
|  | | +---------+ | |  |
|  | | | Content | | |  |
|  | | +---------+ | |  |
|  | +-------------+ |  |
|  +-----------------+  |
+-----------------------+
1. Width and Height
.box {
    width: 300px;
    height: 150px;
}

Example:

<div class="box">
    Hello CSS
</div>
.box {
    width: 300px;
    height: 150px;
    background-color: lightblue;
}
2. Border

Adds a border around an element.

.box {
    border: 2px solid black;
}

Syntax:

border: width style color;

Examples:

border: 1px solid black;
border: 3px dashed red;
border: 5px dotted blue;
3. Padding

Space inside the border.

.box {
    padding: 20px;
}

Example:

<div class="box">
    Java Developer
</div>
.box {
    border: 2px solid black;
    padding: 20px;
}

👉 Text moves away from the border.

4. Margin

Space outside the border.

.box {
    margin: 20px;
}

👉 Creates distance between elements.

